--- !u!114 &1114585177
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1114585175}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "<align=\"center\"><b><color=#2E2E2E>Enemy Proximity Detection</color></b>\r\n<size=85%><i><color=#555555>An
    efficient system for nearest neighbor detection.</color></i></size></align>\r\n<line-height=1.1>\r\n<b><color=#005A9C>Shortcuts</color></b>\r\n\n<color=#2E2E2E><E>
    Add 50 enemies</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E><R> Remove 50 enemies</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E><LMB>
    Spawn one enemy</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E><RMB> Look around</color>\r\n\n\r<b><color=#005A9C>SYSTEM
    OVERVIEW</color></b>\r\n\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>This system demonstrates how to efficiently
    find the nearest enemy for all units using a Spatial Hashing grid structure.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022
    <b>Spatial Hashing Manager:</b> Organizes all enemies into a grid of cells, speeding
    up location-based queries.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022 <b>Enemy Proximity
    Detector:</b> Manages the process of finding the nearest enemy for each unit,
    distributing the computation over several frames.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022
    <b>Enemy:</b> The individual units that move, register with the system, and can
    visually indicate when they detect a nearby foe.</color>\r\n\r\n<b><color=#005A9C>HOW
    TO SET UP</color></b>\r\n\r\n<color=#2E2E2E><b>1. SpatialHashingManager:</b>
    Attach the <b>SpatialHashingManager.cs</b> script to an empty GameObject (e.g.,
    \"<color=#3D3D3D>GameManager</color>\").</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>   \u2022
    Set <b>Cell Size:</b> (e.g., <color=#3D3D3D>20</color>) - Defines the grid cell
    dimensions.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#2E2E2E><b>2. EnemyProximityDetector:</b> Attach
    the <b>EnemyProximityDetector.cs</b> script to another empty GameObject (e.g.,
    \"<color=#3D3D3D>DetectionSystem</color>\").</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>   \u2022
    Set <b>Search Radius Per Enemy:</b> (e.g., <color=#3D3D3D>25</color>) - The distance
    each enemy looks for others.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>   \u2022 Set <b>Enemies
    Per Frame Slice:</b> (e.g., <color=#3D3D3D>10</color>) - Controls performance
    by spreading updates.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#2E2E2E><b>3. Enemy Prefab:</b> Ensure
    your Enemy Prefab has the <b>Enemy.cs</b> script attached.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>  
    \u2022 Set <b>Move Speed:</b> (e.g., <color=#3D3D3D>3-5</color>).\r\n   \u2022
    Set <b>Min/Max Direction Change Time:</b> (e.g., <color=#3D3D3D>5</color> & <color=#3D3D3D>10</color>)
    - For random movement behavior.</color>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><color=#005A9C>HOW IT WORKS
    (IN PLAY MODE)</color></b>\r\n\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022 <b>Autonomous Movement:</b>
    Enemies will wander randomly, changing direction every few seconds.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022
    <b>Proximity Detection:</b> The system continuously runs, finding the nearest
    enemy for each unit. This work is intelligently spread across multiple frames
    to maintain smooth performance.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022 <b>Detection
    Visuals:</b> When an enemy successfully detects another enemy within its search
    radius, its attached <b>Trail Renderer</b> will activate and draw a dynamic,
    fading trail behind it as it moves. When no nearest enemy is found, the trail
    deactivates.</color>\r\n<color=#2E2E2E>\u2022 <b>Scene View Debugging (Gizmos):</b>
    In the Scene View, you'll see <b>blue wire spheres</b> around enemies indicating
    their <b>Search Radius</b>, and <b>blue lines</b> connecting enemies to their
    currently detected nearest neighbor.</color>\r"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
